<subSubSection id="C3306530FFA4DF35B3B17D96FCD8FE52" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9536BBFFA4DF35B3B17D96FCD8FE52" blockId="8.[191,1442,1729,1927]" lastBlockId="9.[192,1440,214,442]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA4DF34B3B17D96FEFDF937" bold="true" box="[192,303,1730,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA4DF34B2497D95FD23F937" authority="Diakonoff, 1988" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[312,753,1729,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA4DF34B2497D95FDE3F930" box="[312,561,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Eucosmocydia oedipus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFA4DF34B14B7D95FD23F937" author="Diakonoff A." box="[570,753,1729,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="307 - 330" refId="ref17832" refString="Diakonoff A. 1988. Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 4 (Lepidoptera). Annales Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 24 (3): 307 - 330." type="journal article" year="1988">Diakonoff, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA4DF34B0847D95FB43F930" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[1013,1169,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA4DF34B0847D95FB43F930" box="[1013,1169,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Eucosmocydia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although we have not examined the 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFA4DF34B22A7DB0FE6DF915" box="[347,447,1764,1790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
, its identity is unambiguous from the original description. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFA4DF34B7AB7DB0FA49F915" author="Diakonoff A." box="[1242,1435,1764,1790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="307 - 330" refId="ref17832" refString="Diakonoff A. 1988. Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 4 (Lepidoptera). Annales Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 24 (3): 307 - 330." type="journal article" year="1988">Diakonoff (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA4DF34B3CE7C53FEE0F8CB" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[191,306,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA4DF34B3CE7C53FEE0F8CB" box="[191,306,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">E. oedipus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a broad-winged species superficially resembling species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA4DF34B7027C52FA72F8CB" authority="Treitschke. The" authorityName="Treitschke. The" box="[1139,1440,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Grapholita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA4DF34B7027C52FB3BF8CB" box="[1139,1257,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Grapholita</emphasis>
Treitschke. The
</taxonomicName>
“forewing is purplish-fuscous, closely and finely striated with pale cinerous (tip of scales).” Wingspan 
<quantity id="4CD29B5EFFA4DF34B6397C7CFA4FF8A9" box="[1352,1437,1832,1858]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. “Hind tibia glossy dark grey, a thick pencil of hair-scales dark grey-bronze, posterior tarsus glossy golden.” “Hind wing dorsal lobe grey, black-tipped.” The male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFA4DF34B0347C38FC28F86D" author="Diakonoff A." box="[837,1018,1900,1926]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="307 - 330" refId="ref17832" refString="Diakonoff A. 1988. Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 4 (Lepidoptera). Annales Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 24 (3): 307 - 330." type="journal article" year="1988">Diakonoff 1988</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17) are typical of several species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA5DF35B3AC7B82FEABFF1B" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[221,377,214,240]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B3AC7B82FEABFF1B" box="[221,377,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Eucosmocydia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from those of the species treated in the present contribution by an even higher tegumen. The valva is slender with a long cucullus, similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA5DF35B0F97BACFBF1FEFA" authorityName="Brown and Razowski" authorityYear="2022" box="[904,1059,247,273]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirimiriana">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B0F97BACFBF1FEFA" box="[904,1059,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E. kirimiriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13112A3EFFA5DF35B7407BA3FB50FEFA" box="[1073,1154,247,273]" captionStart="Figures 20–27" captionStartId="15.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[207,1425,213,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[207,1425,213,1773]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 20–27. Male genitalia of Eucosmocydia. 20) E. pappeana, USNM slide 153,769. 21) E. deinbolliana, USNM slide 153,700. 22) E. ugandensis, slide NHMO 3762. 23) E. lecaniodiscana, USNM slide 124,465. 24) Male genitalia of E. nigeriana, USNM slide 153,740.25) Male genitalia of E. pancoviana, USNM slide 153,695.26) Male genitalia of E. chlorobathra, USNM slide 153,691. 27) Male genitalia of E. kirimiriana, USNM slide 143,441." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533442/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFA5DF35B6747BA3FE5FFED8" author="Razowski J &amp; Trematerra P." pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref18592" refString="Razowski J, Trematerra P. 2008. On some Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Mozambique. Redia 91: 33 - 40." type="journal article" year="2008">Razowski and Trematerra (2008)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA5DF35B28C7A4EFDBFFED8" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[509,621,281,307]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B28C7A4EFDBFFED8" box="[509,621,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E. oedipus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFA5DF35B1C37A4DFC95FED8" box="[690,839,281,307]" name="Mozambique" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, their illustration of the male genitalia does not agree with Diakonoff ’s (1988) figure. The cucullus of the valva in the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFA5DF35B75F7A6FFB13FEBE" box="[1070,1217,315,341]" name="Mozambique" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B4AFFA5DF35B7BF7A6FFE85FE9D" author="Razowski J &amp; Trematerra P." pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref18592" refString="Razowski J, Trematerra P. 2008. On some Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Mozambique. Redia 91: 33 - 40." type="journal article" year="2008">Razowski and Trematerra 2008</bibRefCitation>
, fig. III, 10) is subrectangular, whereas the shape of the valva in the 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFA5DF35B73E7A08FB63FE9D" box="[1103,1201,348,374]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA5DF35B7A77A09FA94FE9D" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[1238,1350,348,375]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B7A77A09FB37FE9D" box="[1238,1253,349,374]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B7827A08FA94FE9D" box="[1267,1350,348,374]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">oedipus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more rounded and apically tapered. Presently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D38FFA5DF35B1E07A2BFCD0FE73" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1988" box="[657,770,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosmocydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B95EEAA9FFA5DF35B1E07A2BFCD0FE73" box="[657,770,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E. oedipus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54918819FFA5DF35B76F7A2AFB52FE73" box="[1054,1152,382,408]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D762BFFA5DF35B7B87A2AFA82FE73" box="[1225,1360,382,408]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. DNAbarcode sequences and the life history are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
